      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 50 九四</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 50 九四</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九四：鼎折足，覆公餗，其形渥，凶。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fourth NINE, undivided, shows the caldron with its feet broken; and its contents, designed for the ruler's use, overturned and spilt. Its Subject will be made to blush for shame. There will be evil.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
